   143  /**
   144   * The group coordinator shard is a replicated state machine that manages the metadata of all
   145   * classic and consumer groups. It holds the hard and the soft state of the groups. This class
   146   * has two kinds of methods:
   147   * 1) The request handlers which handle the requests and generate a response and records to
   148   *    mutate the hard state. Those records will be written by the runtime and applied to the
   149   *    hard state via the replay methods.
   150   * 2) The replay methods which apply records to the hard state. Those are used in the request
   151   *    handling as well as during the initial loading of the records from the partitions.
   152   */
